ActHeritage Railway Stations Protection Act
SubjectOrder authorizing the Canadian Pacific Railway Company (CPR) to sell the Windsor Station in Montreal, Quebec.
PrecisRepeal of Order in Council P.C. 2008-1742 of November 10, 2008 and Order authorizing Canadian Pacific Railway Company to sell the Windsor railway station in Montreal, Quebec, to The Cadillac Fairview Corporation Limited, or a Canadian body corporate or partnership that is owned or controlled by the Cadillac Fairview Corporation Limitedor that is an affiliate of it.
